2
00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.480
US, US

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.340
US, ALL OF US

4
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:15.770
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

5
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:18.530
We all have different places we want to go

6
00:00:16.370 --> 00:00:17.750
We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

7
00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:21.310
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

8
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:25.660
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

9
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.250
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

10
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.530
ONE PIECE!!

11
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:33.510
ALL OF US, I've got a question for you
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

12
00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:37.100
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

13
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:45.300
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

14
00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:52.030
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

15
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.620
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

16
00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:55.150
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

17
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.200
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

18
00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:02.580
Random clues suddenly fit together

19
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

20
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

21
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

22
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

23
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

24
00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:34.490
<b>The Legendary Hero</b>

25
00:01:35.070 --> 00:01:36.280
Big news!

26
00:01:36.280 --> 00:01:40.160
<b>Beehive, the Pirate Island
New World</b>

27
00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:38.950
Captain Koby has escaped!

28
00:01:38.950 --> 00:01:40.160
Seriously?!

29
00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:46.000
He escaped, so he's not
the commodore's prize anymore, right?!

30
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.590
How much will we get if we capture him?!

31
00:01:50.340 --> 00:01:54.050
Well, we don't need to put a bounty on him!

32
00:01:54.050 --> 00:01:56.550
Cross Guild will pay it for us!

33
00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:59.430
I bought odds on him with a win ticket!

34
00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:01.390
The payout's gonna be big!

35
00:02:01.390 --> 00:02:03.390
How much will we get if we kill him?!

36
00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:05.690
Wait till you hear this!

37
00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:09.820
He's a five-star bounty!

38
00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:13.490
That means five treasure chests!
A total of 500 million berries!

39
00:02:13.490 --> 00:02:16.120
A five-star bounty?!

40
00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:18.330
Captains are usually only worth one!

41
00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:24.170
Alright! Let's hit the jackpot!

42
00:02:24.170 --> 00:02:27.040
Let the hunt begin!

43
00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:32.380
I'm feeline a tickle on
the left side of my chest.

44
00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:36.010
That's where the slaves are
held before they're sold...

45
00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:44.310
Are they breaking out?!

46
00:02:44.640 --> 00:02:46.810
The slaves escaped?!

47
00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:50.020
Can we hunt them, Pizarro?!

48
00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:51.650
Don't be stupid!

49
00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:53.490
You guys are so greedy!

50
00:02:54.030 --> 00:02:55.740
Bring them all back!

51
00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:57.200
Don't even kill Koby...

52
00:02:57.660 --> 00:02:59.280
or I'll tell Teach!

53
00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:04.080
Why is that mountain talking...?

54
00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:06.580
He knows that we're here!

55
00:03:06.580 --> 00:03:07.790
Let's hurry!

56
00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:11.750
What?

57
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:14.720
This is it for us...

58
00:03:15.170 --> 00:03:19.720
Just run away before we slow you down.

59
00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:21.930
Don't give up hope.

60
00:03:21.930 --> 00:03:24.310
I'll lure them all away...

61
00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:28.940
so make sure everyone escapes!

62
00:03:28.940 --> 00:03:29.690
Well then...

63
00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:32.280
We'll meet again!

64
00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:35.820
Thanks!

65
00:03:38.070 --> 00:03:40.280
Thank you, Captain Koby...

66
00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:45.660
You're a saint!

67
00:03:50.630 --> 00:03:53.550
<b>Shiryu of the Rain
Clear-Clear Fruit
Invisible Man</b>

68
00:03:53.550 --> 00:03:58.130
You should have captured
them yourself, Pizarro.

69
00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:05.480
Like I said, Teach would be pissed.

70
00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:08.480
<b>"Corrupt King" Avalo Pizarro
Isle-Isle Fruit
Island Man</b>

71
00:04:08.480 --> 00:04:12.110
I just break things whenever I meowve.

72
00:04:12.110 --> 00:04:12.940
Huh?

73
00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:18.860
Mind if I take a shot?

74
00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:22.070
Vasco Shot... What are mew gonna do?

75
00:04:28.290 --> 00:04:32.040
They can't run if I burn down the town.

76
00:04:31.580 --> 00:04:35.130
<b>"Heavy Drinker" Vasco Shot
Glug-Glug Fruit
Booze Man</b>

77
00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:46.060
Hey, don't do that!
That would be a meowssive fire!

78
00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:48.520
Teach would be furrious!

79
00:04:48.520 --> 00:04:51.270
It's fine. Leave it to me.

80
00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:56.360
Furget it! We just finished
fixing up Rocky Port!

81
00:04:56.860 --> 00:05:00.240
Would you rather leave it to Wolf?

82
00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:05.830
Wolf?

83
00:05:05.830 --> 00:05:10.040
<b>"Colossal Battleship" Sanjuan Wolf
Huge-Huge Fruit
Gigantification Man</b>

84
00:05:07.700 --> 00:05:10.040
That's meowt of the question!

85
00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:13.040
Mew might as well just
destroy the whole town!

86
00:05:17.670 --> 00:05:18.760
I found him!

87
00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:26.760
Damn! I guess I can't outrun them!

88
00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:30.230
Somehow...

89
00:05:31.270 --> 00:05:36.570
I have to keep them busy until
everyone can escape to the sea!

90
00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:40.950
Koby the Hero!

91
00:05:44.870 --> 00:05:49.700
Koby the Hero, I want to turn this island...

92
00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:54.000
this Pirate Island...

93
00:05:54.380 --> 00:05:58.210
into a full-fledged nation!

94
00:05:58.210 --> 00:06:02.430
A World Government-affiliated nation!

95
00:06:03.680 --> 00:06:05.390
It'll be the Blackbeard Kingdom...

96
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.760
with me as its king!

97
00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:13.190
How's that?

98
00:06:13.190 --> 00:06:15.270
Stop this nonsense.

99
00:06:15.650 --> 00:06:17.770
There's no way it would work!

100
00:06:18.190 --> 00:06:20.230
It'd be a country of criminals!

101
00:06:20.610 --> 00:06:24.610
Hey, don't step on a man's dream!

102
00:06:24.610 --> 00:06:28.620
I'll negotiate with them
using you as a bargaining chip.

103
00:06:29.910 --> 00:06:33.660
If the government or the Marines
give in to terrorists, we're all doomed!

104
00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:37.000
Anyway, you're wasting your time.

105
00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:38.920
Because...

106
00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:41.590
I'm a member of SWORD!

107
00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:44.680
SWORD?

108
00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:46.390
What the hell is that?

109
00:06:46.390 --> 00:06:47.930
Oh, I see...

110
00:06:47.930 --> 00:06:48.640
Huh?

111
00:06:48.640 --> 00:06:50.640
This isn't gonna go well.

112
00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:52.980
Give up on the trade, Teach.

113
00:07:00.650 --> 00:07:02.190
What he means...

114
00:07:02.190 --> 00:07:05.240
is that he's a Marine but also not.

115
00:07:06.530 --> 00:07:08.990
He gave up his Marine code.

116
00:07:11.200 --> 00:07:15.750
SWORD is a group of Marines that have
already submitted their resignations.

117
00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:20.340
Which means they could even fight
the Four Emperors without permission.

118
00:07:20.340 --> 00:07:24.670
They can operate however they choose
and disregard any and all orders.

119
00:07:24.670 --> 00:07:25.880
They're free agents.

120
00:07:26.380 --> 00:07:27.890
In exchange...

121
00:07:29.100 --> 00:07:32.930
the Marines are in no way
responsible for their actions...

122
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:35.690
and can fire them anytime.

123
00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:39.650
I see!

124
00:07:40.150 --> 00:07:43.900
So there's the normal idiots who
sit around waiting for permission,

125
00:07:44.320 --> 00:07:47.740
and you guys, who charge in
without thinking twice!

126
00:07:50.200 --> 00:07:52.870
Now that I get it, I like your style!

127
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:55.200
But...

128
00:07:55.200 --> 00:07:57.830
I'm not gonna change the plan!

129
00:07:58.420 --> 00:08:00.210
I'll do it anyway!

130
00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:03.630
Even if you're in SWORD,

131
00:08:04.340 --> 00:08:07.880
the people still call you a hero.

132
00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:11.300
I wonder if the Marines can
really afford to just abandon you.

133
00:08:12.100 --> 00:08:14.560
Let's ask the public, shall we?!

134
00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:18.730
That way the government can't just
wash their hands of this!

135
00:08:22.110 --> 00:08:24.820
Until then, lock him up!

136
00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:28.070
I can't wait!

137
00:08:28.070 --> 00:08:30.780
Don't let him escape!

138
00:08:32.530 --> 00:08:35.370
Get back here, Koby!

139
00:08:41.540 --> 00:08:42.420
Hey!

140
00:08:42.420 --> 00:08:48.720
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

141
00:08:49.300 --> 00:08:51.510
I may have cooperated with a pirate...

142
00:08:52.010 --> 00:08:54.390
but you gotta do what you gotta do!

143
00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:02.860
What's that?

144
00:09:12.530 --> 00:09:15.240
Three Marines spotted at the port!

145
00:09:15.740 --> 00:09:18.290
What? Marines?! No way!

146
00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:20.250
Hurry up!

147
00:09:21.290 --> 00:09:23.880
They're strong! Be careful!

148
00:09:25.670 --> 00:09:27.800
Did someone come to rescue me?

149
00:09:27.800 --> 00:09:29.130
No, no!

150
00:09:29.130 --> 00:09:30.800
How arrogant of me!

151
00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:32.010
I'm ashamed!

152
00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:52.820
Who are they?!

153
00:09:52.820 --> 00:09:54.320
Why are they so strong?!

154
00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:56.830
They're heading toward
the center of the town!

155
00:09:56.830 --> 00:09:57.790
What do they want?!

156
00:09:57.790 --> 00:10:00.200
Who cares?! Stop them!

157
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:08.800
What?

158
00:10:08.800 --> 00:10:10.260
Guns don't work on them!

159
00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:14.050
That's as far as you go!

160
00:10:17.470 --> 00:10:19.060
He cut his head off!

161
00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:25.270
I took one down!

162
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:26.980
That'll teach you!

163
00:10:33.570 --> 00:10:34.860
That hurt...

164
00:10:34.860 --> 00:10:35.870
What?!

165
00:10:35.870 --> 00:10:36.990
A logia?!

166
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:38.870
What's with this guy?!

167
00:10:38.870 --> 00:10:41.160
It's like he's made of clay!

168
00:10:42.710 --> 00:10:45.080
Where are you, Koby?!

169
00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:49.040
H-Hey...

170
00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:51.800
Are those buildings moving?!

171
00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:53.550
No, stupid! Of course not!

172
00:10:53.550 --> 00:10:55.510
You drink too much!

173
00:11:02.850 --> 00:11:05.310
Go on! Be a good little boy!

174
00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:10.190
Get a move on!

175
00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:13.150
What a weird lady. Who is that?

176
00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:15.950
Come on, straighten up!

177
00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:20.580
You look pathetic!

178
00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:22.700
Come on! Come on! Come on!

179
00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:25.210
She's whipping a building...

180
00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:28.630
What is it? Staring, are we?

181
00:11:28.630 --> 00:11:30.340
What? No, I...

182
00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:33.050
S-She's a Marine?!

183
00:11:39.800 --> 00:11:43.470
Is it that rare for a pirate
to set eyes on a Marine?

184
00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:46.480
<b>Rear Admiral Kujaku
Marine Headquarters (SWORD)
Granddaughter of "Master Tactician" Tsuru
Whip-Whip Fruit
Discipline Woman</b>

185
00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:48.730
Come to me.

186
00:11:48.730 --> 00:11:50.230
You're so cute.

187
00:11:57.820 --> 00:11:59.700
I'll whip you into shape.

188
00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:09.170
You're cornered, Koby!

189
00:12:09.540 --> 00:12:11.670
Oh no! I'm surrounded!

190
00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:18.340
Take aim!

191
00:12:20.590 --> 00:12:21.550
Is this it for me?

192
00:12:22.050 --> 00:12:23.760
On my mark!

193
00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.350
Fire!

194
00:12:38.070 --> 00:12:38.650
What?!

195
00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:40.200
What?

196
00:12:41.450 --> 00:12:43.160
What?

197
00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:48.580
What? What?

198
00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:50.870
What?!

199
00:12:54.460 --> 00:12:56.050
It's beautiful!

200
00:12:56.050 --> 00:12:57.130
Wait, no!

201
00:12:57.130 --> 00:12:58.510
What the hell is this?!

202
00:12:58.920 --> 00:13:01.260
Why did a flower come out of the muzzle?!

203
00:13:02.510 --> 00:13:04.760
No, wait...

204
00:13:04.760 --> 00:13:05.930
This is...

205
00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:11.230
one of Dr. Vegapunk's inventions!

206
00:13:15.650 --> 00:13:18.780
It earned him the Mobel Peace Prize!

207
00:13:19.820 --> 00:13:21.910
That's not what I'm asking!

208
00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:24.870
Who did this?!

209
00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:26.080
Koby!

210
00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:31.500
Get over here!

211
00:13:31.500 --> 00:13:32.210
Wait, no!

212
00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:34.420
I didn't mean anythin' weird!

213
00:13:34.590 --> 00:13:38.380
<b>Commander Hibari
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>

214
00:13:38.380 --> 00:13:41.180
Hibari! What are you doing here?!

215
00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:42.800
Don't tell me...

216
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:43.930
Yes!

217
00:13:43.930 --> 00:13:47.510
I shot them with flower rounds,
which cause gunpowder to bloom!

218
00:13:47.850 --> 00:13:50.020
They can't use their weapons!

219
00:13:50.020 --> 00:13:51.980
Run while you can!

220
00:13:52.440 --> 00:13:54.860
A-And...

221
00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:56.690
if you're hungry, I...

222
00:13:57.070 --> 00:13:58.320
made...

223
00:13:59.690 --> 00:14:01.070
lunch for you!

224
00:14:01.070 --> 00:14:02.150
Huh?

225
00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:04.660
No, I mean...

226
00:14:12.250 --> 00:14:13.620
Prince! Any progress?

227
00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:17.840
Yeah, we just finished up here.

228
00:14:21.510 --> 00:14:25.260
<b>Rear Admiral Prince Grus</b>
<b>Marine Headquarters</b>

229
00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:27.720
<b>Glorp-Glorp Fruit</b>
<b>Clay Man</b>

230
00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:27.140
Koby is safe, too!

231
00:14:27.720 --> 00:14:30.180
<b>Mud Puppet (Golem)</b>

232
00:14:30.560 --> 00:14:34.020
H-Hey... Has this square
always been shaped like this?

233
00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:34.650
What?

234
00:14:37.360 --> 00:14:40.360
Isn't that building moving?

235
00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:41.820
H-Hey, wait!

236
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:46.870
O-Oh no...

237
00:14:46.870 --> 00:14:48.950
We can't get out of here!

238
00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:50.950
Now, whenever you're ready!

239
00:14:51.330 --> 00:14:52.910
Head to the very center!

240
00:14:53.290 --> 00:14:55.250
I was able to contact Prince!

241
00:14:55.580 --> 00:14:57.000
It's all ready!

242
00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:58.500
Vice Admiral Garp!

243
00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:02.510
Everyone, hang onto something!

244
00:15:05.090 --> 00:15:07.390
Charge!

245
00:15:15.690 --> 00:15:17.020
C'mon! Hurry up!

246
00:15:17.440 --> 00:15:19.270
Let's get out of here!

247
00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:26.530
Look up!

248
00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:33.290
Whaaat?!

249
00:15:35.870 --> 00:15:40.040
– Whaaat?!
– Whaaat?!

250
00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:44.380
A Marine ship is flying through the sky!

251
00:15:44.380 --> 00:15:47.050
Why?! How is that possible?!

252
00:15:47.050 --> 00:15:48.390
Who's on it?!

253
00:15:49.850 --> 00:15:52.760
Isn't it... falling toward us?

254
00:15:52.760 --> 00:15:55.310
R-Run!

255
00:15:59.020 --> 00:16:00.150
Look!

256
00:16:00.150 --> 00:16:01.650
On the ship!

257
00:16:04.440 --> 00:16:07.910
No way! I thought he retired!

258
00:16:08.410 --> 00:16:09.870
The legendary...

259
00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:11.450
Hero!

260
00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:19.540
Vice Admiral Garp!

261
00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:21.540
Koby!

262
00:16:21.540 --> 00:16:23.550
I'm here to save you!

263
00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:28.050
Run! Just run!

264
00:16:28.050 --> 00:16:29.010
We can't...

265
00:16:29.010 --> 00:16:30.970
There's no way out!

266
00:16:34.560 --> 00:16:38.100
Hey, you damn pirates!

267
00:16:38.940 --> 00:16:41.060
He's coming! Run!

268
00:16:59.960 --> 00:17:01.830
Vice Admiral Garp...

269
00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:05.960
Why? I'm not even worth saving...

270
00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:07.970
You idiots!

271
00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:13.930
Do you have any idea who
the hell you've kidnapped?!

272
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:25.230
Koby is the future of the Marines!

273
00:17:26.400 --> 00:17:29.030
Not to mention...

274
00:17:29.490 --> 00:17:33.620
my precious protégé!

275
00:17:34.990 --> 00:17:38.290
Galaxy...

276
00:17:49.460 --> 00:17:53.340
Impact!

277
00:18:52.150 --> 00:18:54.700
Cumulo-glorpus!

278
00:19:07.670 --> 00:19:09.670
Damn you, Garp!

279
00:19:09.670 --> 00:19:11.250
He's insane!

280
00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:13.510
I'll make that geezer pay!

281
00:19:13.510 --> 00:19:15.220
Don't move, pirates!

282
00:19:16.180 --> 00:19:19.930
Resistance will only result in further damage!

283
00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:29.440
Absolutely pathetic...

284
00:19:30.230 --> 00:19:32.230
I've really gotten rusty.

285
00:19:32.860 --> 00:19:34.240
Screw you!

286
00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:36.860
As if there's anything left to damage!

287
00:19:37.240 --> 00:19:39.200
Vice Admiral Garp!

288
00:19:40.990 --> 00:19:42.540
Oh, Koby!

289
00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:44.960
You're okay!

290
00:19:47.210 --> 00:19:49.080
Thank goodness!

291
00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:51.460
They didn't kill him!

292
00:19:51.460 --> 00:19:53.090
Really now...

293
00:19:53.090 --> 00:19:54.590
He overdid it.

294
00:19:54.590 --> 00:19:57.470
You're such a naughty boy, Garp!

295
00:19:57.470 --> 00:20:01.430
Garp said Koby's the future of
the Marines. I won't stand for it!

296
00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:03.640
I'm gonna sabotage him!

297
00:20:03.640 --> 00:20:08.150
That's something you're supposed
to keep to yourself, you spoiled brat.

298
00:20:08.150 --> 00:20:09.770
It's cuter that way.

299
00:20:09.770 --> 00:20:11.860
Koby!

300
00:20:11.860 --> 00:20:14.150
Captain Koby!

301
00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:16.610
Koby!

302
00:20:16.610 --> 00:20:18.320
Tashigi!

303
00:20:18.700 --> 00:20:21.070
Even non-SWORD members came...

304
00:20:22.200 --> 00:20:25.160
Hey, Koby! Why are you
lugging that thing around?

305
00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:26.500
Vice Admiral Garp!

306
00:20:26.910 --> 00:20:30.580
We've tried everything,
but we can't get the shackle off!!

307
00:20:30.580 --> 00:20:31.540
Please...

308
00:20:33.920 --> 00:20:35.260
do...

309
00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:37.090
some...

310
00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:39.840
thing...

311
00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:45.140
Hibari...!

312
00:20:45.140 --> 00:20:46.350
Hibari!

313
00:20:49.730 --> 00:20:51.020
Hibari!

314
00:21:03.070 --> 00:21:04.330
Kuzan.

315
00:21:04.830 --> 00:21:06.290
Kuzan!

316
00:21:06.620 --> 00:21:08.040
What are you doing?!

317
00:21:08.040 --> 00:21:10.540
Please thaw her out right now!

318
00:21:12.130 --> 00:21:14.130
It's Aokiji!

319
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:17.260
Captain Kuzan!

320
00:21:17.260 --> 00:21:19.090
Kuzan!

321
00:21:20.470 --> 00:21:22.340
Don't get me in trouble, Koby.

322
00:21:22.340 --> 00:21:24.260
I can't have you running off...

323
00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:27.390
while Teach is away.

324
00:21:28.100 --> 00:21:33.900
Two years ago, Admiral Akainu and Admiral Aokiji...

325
00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:40.570
fought for the position of the next
fleet admiral of Marine Headquarters.

326
00:21:44.700 --> 00:21:49.080
The deadly struggle went on for
ten days before a victor emerged:

327
00:21:49.750 --> 00:21:50.790
Akainu.

328
00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:57.090
However, Aokiji refused to serve under him.

329
00:21:57.460 --> 00:21:59.460
And so, he left the Marines.

330
00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:10.560
<b>Some Island, New World</b>

331
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:21.440
What the...?!

332
00:22:21.780 --> 00:22:23.570
Blackbeard's here!

333
00:22:23.570 --> 00:22:26.370
Run! Get out of the town!

334
00:22:26.370 --> 00:22:27.280
Hey!

335
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.490
What happened here?

336
00:22:29.490 --> 00:22:32.460
Wait! Who did this?!

337
00:22:36.590 --> 00:22:39.050
No, I don't need to ask...

338
00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:45.800
There's only one person
in the world who could've done this!

339
00:22:47.760 --> 00:22:49.220
It's you!

340
00:22:49.220 --> 00:22:51.270
Aokiji!

341
00:23:03.860 --> 00:23:06.490
My crew is frozen solid outside!

342
00:23:06.490 --> 00:23:08.910
Undo it!

343
00:23:09.780 --> 00:23:12.370
You're annoying me.

344
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:16.000
And don't even think about using your power.

345
00:23:17.500 --> 00:23:19.790
Your crew will shatter and die.

346
00:23:21.300 --> 00:23:24.550
You're their captain, so I think you know.

347
00:23:25.800 --> 00:23:28.260
Do you really think I started it?

348
00:23:29.010 --> 00:23:31.970
Besides, you already know, don't you?

349
00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:36.900
I'm not just heartbroken, I'm furious.

350
00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:41.860
Take a guess who actually started this.

351
00:24:05.670 --> 00:24:08.130
Another round over here!

352
00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:12.930
You can really knock 'em back, Ice Pop!

353
00:24:12.930 --> 00:24:15.680
You're not bad yourself, you son of a bitch!

354
00:24:18.140 --> 00:24:21.270
So what did Akainu say next?

355
00:24:24.900 --> 00:24:28.030
"Two men who enlisted the same year
in a fight to the death...

356
00:24:28.030 --> 00:24:31.240
My eyes are burning with tears."

357
00:24:31.950 --> 00:24:34.950
And I said, "Yeah, that's 'cause...

358
00:24:35.290 --> 00:24:38.000
your magma's flowing!"

359
00:24:40.170 --> 00:24:41.670
And now look at me!

360
00:24:45.590 --> 00:24:47.550
I'm down to one leg!

361
00:24:48.470 --> 00:24:51.430
So that's what happens
when two admirals fight!

362
00:24:51.430 --> 00:24:52.970
What about Akainu?

363
00:24:53.510 --> 00:24:55.890
Did you at least rip one of his arms off?!

364
00:24:56.270 --> 00:24:57.270
No...

365
00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:02.610
But I'm sure he's scarred to all hell.

366
00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:09.530
Speaking of scars, he might know
Burn Scar, Commodore.

367
00:25:09.900 --> 00:25:12.030
Huh? Burn Scar?

368
00:25:12.030 --> 00:25:17.830
There are four important
red lode poneglyphs in the world.

369
00:25:19.960 --> 00:25:24.630
Big Mom and Kaido have two of them...

370
00:25:26.250 --> 00:25:30.590
But we can't find the other two!

371
00:25:30.590 --> 00:25:33.340
Once more fate rears its head...

372
00:25:33.340 --> 00:25:34.300
Yeah...

373
00:25:34.300 --> 00:25:40.310
And they say that the Man with
the Burn Scar has one of them.

374
00:25:42.020 --> 00:25:43.190
Is it me?

375
00:25:43.190 --> 00:25:45.570
You just got that scar, you idiot!

376
00:25:50.240 --> 00:25:52.240
Rumor has it...

377
00:25:58.540 --> 00:26:03.370
that he sails a pitch-black ship.

378
00:26:10.340 --> 00:26:16.050
And when you get close, he creates
a giant whirlpool to swallow you up.

379
00:26:20.850 --> 00:26:23.560
He may have eaten a devil fruit...

380
00:26:24.190 --> 00:26:27.770
I believe he works for the government.

381
00:26:28.270 --> 00:26:31.820
The World Government has
dark secrets, after all.

382
00:26:31.820 --> 00:26:34.700
If they hold on to even one of the stones,

383
00:26:34.700 --> 00:26:43.250
it means that no pirate will ever reach the
One Piece, the single greatest hidden treasure.

384
00:26:44.750 --> 00:26:48.630
The poneglyphs... I only have
bitter memories involving them.

385
00:26:48.630 --> 00:26:54.300
If I saw a red stone like that
in Ohara, I'd remember it.

386
00:26:55.930 --> 00:26:58.050
All I can remember...

387
00:26:58.050 --> 00:27:01.310
is a good friend who rebelled
against the government...

388
00:27:01.310 --> 00:27:04.140
and a girl with eyes full of despair...

389
00:27:04.640 --> 00:27:08.400
whose fate was in my hands.

390
00:27:10.730 --> 00:27:13.610
What kind of boring story is that?!

391
00:27:16.450 --> 00:27:18.660
Commodore, what should we do?

392
00:27:18.660 --> 00:27:19.280
Huh?

393
00:27:19.660 --> 00:27:24.000
If we take his power for ourselves,
it'll be a considerable asset to us...

394
00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:32.420
I heard that, you slimy bastards!

395
00:27:34.630 --> 00:27:38.600
How about I send you to an icy hell?!

396
00:27:42.140 --> 00:27:43.520
Stop, stop, stop!

397
00:27:45.060 --> 00:27:50.860
That's right, I've already heard about
you guys hunting devil fruit powers.

398
00:27:52.280 --> 00:27:54.030
Bring it on!

399
00:27:59.660 --> 00:28:00.870
Wait!

400
00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:02.990
I'm sorry!

401
00:28:02.990 --> 00:28:05.750
What my crew member said was ridiculous.

402
00:28:06.370 --> 00:28:08.920
I wouldn't dream of doing that.

403
00:28:08.920 --> 00:28:11.040
What I really wanted to ask you was...

404
00:28:11.040 --> 00:28:13.500
Do you wanna sail with us?

405
00:28:14.460 --> 00:28:17.720
What?! Captain, are you off your rocker?!

406
00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:20.680
You lost your position, didn't you?

407
00:28:20.680 --> 00:28:22.680
Do you have a place to go?

408
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.680
What are you gonna do now?

409
00:28:24.680 --> 00:28:27.100
The guardians of justice have abandoned you!

410
00:28:28.140 --> 00:28:30.270
Man, this must be rock bottom.

411
00:28:30.270 --> 00:28:34.150
A pirate worrying about my prospects.

412
00:28:34.150 --> 00:28:37.360
Wherever you go, whatever you do,

413
00:28:37.990 --> 00:28:41.120
trouble will always find you!

414
00:28:41.120 --> 00:28:46.290
So what flag are you gonna fight under?

415
00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:47.710
Huh?!

416
00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:52.090
I'm different from the Marines!

417
00:28:52.090 --> 00:28:54.920
I have my own brand of justice!

418
00:28:54.920 --> 00:28:56.260
Don't be stupid!

419
00:28:56.260 --> 00:29:01.260
Just because we shared a few drinks
doesn't mean I trust scum like you!

420
00:29:01.260 --> 00:29:02.640
Whoa, whoa!

421
00:29:02.640 --> 00:29:05.520
I think you have the wrong idea about pirates.

422
00:29:05.520 --> 00:29:09.520
It's not like we're all buddies here!

423
00:29:14.690 --> 00:29:16.900
The only thing a pirate crew needs...

424
00:29:19.570 --> 00:29:23.740
is to have mutual interests!

425
00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:29.750
You're free now...

426
00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:33.170
so what do you wanna do?

427
00:29:47.720 --> 00:29:49.350
Hey, Kuzan!

428
00:29:49.810 --> 00:29:51.640
Thaw out Hibari!

429
00:29:52.190 --> 00:29:53.980
Let Koby escape!

430
00:29:53.980 --> 00:29:56.690
Come back to the Marines!

431
00:29:59.440 --> 00:30:04.570
You haven't changed at all.
Always saying what's on your mind.

432
00:30:08.290 --> 00:30:12.370
But I can't let any of that happen, Garp!

433
00:30:13.290 --> 00:30:15.080
I've always loved...

434
00:30:15.960 --> 00:30:17.800
how straightforward you are...

435
00:30:18.420 --> 00:30:22.720
which is why I'm living the way I want to now!

436
00:30:19.710 --> 00:30:22.720
<b>Kuzan
Captain of the Tenth Ship
Blackbeard Pirates</b>

437
00:30:27.930 --> 00:30:29.310
Bonehead...

438
00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:46.870
Ice...

439
00:30:47.370 --> 00:30:48.580
Ball!

440
00:30:54.830 --> 00:30:56.790
Vice Admiral Garp!

441
00:30:58.960 --> 00:31:00.800
Vice Admiral Garp!

442
00:31:04.260 --> 00:31:06.890
In order to save your beloved protégé,

443
00:31:07.470 --> 00:31:11.970
can you kill your former star pupil?!

444
00:31:13.680 --> 00:31:15.900
Don't live in the past, you moron!

445
00:31:17.520 --> 00:31:20.780
I taught you to live in the moment!

446
00:31:26.160 --> 00:31:27.240
It didn't work!

447
00:31:47.470 --> 00:31:49.220
Listen, Kuzan!

448
00:32:12.410 --> 00:32:14.620
Wavering is a sign...

449
00:32:16.370 --> 00:32:17.330
of weakness!

450
00:32:19.540 --> 00:32:22.960
Blue Hole!

451
00:32:51.950 --> 00:32:57.120
<b>Winner Island
New World</b>

452
00:32:51.950 --> 00:32:55.660
Meanwhile, at Winner Island...

453
00:33:32.450 --> 00:33:37.330
You can hardly call yourself
a pirate crew without a ship!

454
00:33:37.830 --> 00:33:40.540
There's no way for you to escape!

455
00:33:41.170 --> 00:33:47.420
The hundred pirates whose hearts
you stole at Rocky Port...

456
00:33:47.420 --> 00:33:52.010
are still living in fear on the Pirate Island!

457
00:33:52.390 --> 00:33:58.600
But if I bring them your heart,
they're sure to raise a toast!

458
00:34:05.480 --> 00:34:07.730
You really made it for me!

459
00:34:07.730 --> 00:34:11.700
But I can't guarantee it'll work.

460
00:34:17.450 --> 00:34:19.080
Now...

461
00:34:19.080 --> 00:34:23.460
I'm having a hard time deciding whether
to sell or use the Op-Op Fruit.

462
00:34:23.460 --> 00:34:26.670
It can even grant me eternal youth, can't it?!

463
00:34:34.430 --> 00:34:37.180
Get your hands...

464
00:34:39.310 --> 00:34:41.060
off my captain!

465
00:34:50.780 --> 00:34:51.940
Bepo...

466
00:34:57.780 --> 00:34:59.910
What?! Sulong?!

467
00:34:59.910 --> 00:35:02.370
No way! The moon isn't even out!

468
00:35:11.920 --> 00:35:13.920
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

469
00:35:30.230 --> 00:35:31.280
Captain!

470
00:35:53.090 --> 00:35:55.380
Dammit! They fled to sea!

471
00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:57.590
Don't let him get away!

472
00:36:04.560 --> 00:36:07.140
Go back, Bepo...

473
00:36:11.610 --> 00:36:15.900
I can't... leave the crew... behind...

474
00:36:15.900 --> 00:36:17.660
I won't go back!

475
00:36:18.410 --> 00:36:20.780
Trust them, Captain!

476
00:36:20.780 --> 00:36:23.580
From that frigid northern port
all the way until now...

477
00:36:25.580 --> 00:36:28.960
we've always survived!

478
00:36:28.960 --> 00:36:30.250
So...

479
00:36:31.540 --> 00:36:34.050
none of us will die here!

480
00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:42.560
We've overcome so much together!

481
00:36:44.640 --> 00:36:46.520
So, Captain!

482
00:36:47.600 --> 00:36:50.190
Don't die!

483
00:36:58.950 --> 00:37:00.530
Please...

484
00:37:01.910 --> 00:37:03.910
don't die!

485
00:37:09.120 --> 00:37:12.840
At Winner Island in the New World...

486
00:37:21.390 --> 00:37:26.100
the Heart Pirates' submarine, the Polar Tang,

487
00:37:26.470 --> 00:37:27.980
was sunk.

488
00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:35.610
The Heart Pirates led by Trafalgar Law...

489
00:37:36.820 --> 00:37:38.320
were defeated.

490
00:37:47.280 --> 00:37:52.370
Running so long lost track of just how long its been

491
00:37:53.220 --> 00:37:59.730
Collected scars while striving not even trying beneath my skin

492
00:38:00.230 --> 00:38:07.150
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead I remember a map

493
00:38:07.230 --> 00:38:13.440
to a treasure still gleaming its within our grasp

494
00:38:13.580 --> 00:38:20.350
Can you feel my heart Feelings I impart

495
00:38:20.310 --> 00:38:27.460
The promises are there theyre deep down but still primed to share

496
00:38:27.590 --> 00:38:36.570
Peerless dreams kept close the dreams that always matter most

497
00:38:36.750 --> 00:38:42.320
Before we set sail why not raise a toast

498
00:38:42.440 --> 00:38:49.350
So I pen this note to you Dear sunrise Ill see you soon

499
00:38:49.510 --> 00:38:56.540
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

500
00:38:56.520 --> 00:39:03.590
And regardless of our age these memries will still remain

501
00:39:03.490 --> 00:39:10.700
Wont forget until this wish makes it to you
